title: Dining and Diving at RumFish Grill at Guy Harvey Outpost
text:
Updated: 3:27 p.m. Friday, Sept. 4, 2015 | Posted: 5:51 a.m. Friday, Sept. 4, 2015 Dining and Diving at RumFish Grill at Guy Harvey Outpost In Partnership with VisitFlorida.com 
Tampa Bay’s newest destination restaurant, the Rumfish Grill at Guy Harvey Outpost, is a fully immersive experience where visitors can eat, drink, shop and explore. The restaurant’s main attraction is a 33,500-gallon aquarium that occupies an entire wall of the dining room, ceiling to floor. The aquarium was built by Wayde King and Brett Raymer of Animal Planet’s hit series Tanked — book a reservation, and you can snorkel in it!
